Escaping the Taliban. Malina from Pakistan tells Audrey Brown what its like to live in the shadow of the war against the Taliban. Ethiopian Famine As hunger again threatens millions in Ethiopia we hear from some of those who survived the famine twenty five years ago. Mi Kyong The woman in South Korea who's trying to change behaviour towards unmarried mothers. The Snow Leopard of Ghana. Kwame Nkrumah-Acheampong the skier from Ghana who's qualified for the Winter Olympics speaks about his dreams of Olympic glory. Show less